        <div class="card"
            style="width:90%; max-width:600px; max-height:85vh; overflow-y:auto; box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); padding:30px; border-color:var(--accent);">
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; margin-bottom:20px;">
                <h3 style="margin:0; color:var(--accent);">Fixture Profile Setup Guide</h3>
                <button class="nav-btn"
                    style="width:30px; height:30px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:0;"
                    onclick="document.getElementById('profile-help-modal').style.display='none'">×</button>
            </div>

            <div style="color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.6; font-size:13px;">
                <p>Welcome to the Fixture Profile Editor! This is where you tell RaveBox how to map its internal logic
                    engine to the physical DMX parameters of your lights.</p>

                <h4 style="color:var(--text); margin-top:20px; margin-bottom:10px;">Channel Types & Triggers</h4>
                <ul style="padding-left:20px; margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--accent);">Static Value / Dimmer:</strong>
                        The most basic setup. Good for simple dimmers or static behaviors that you just want to set to a
                        number.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--accent);">Continuous Wave (LFO):</strong>
                        Uses an internal oscillator. Recommended for <em>Pan/Tilt</em> movements, <em>color
                            cycling</em>, and smooth effects. Uses sine, triangle, sawtooth, or square waves.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--accent);">Direct: Bass Energy:</strong>
                        Directly hooks the DMX value to the live bass frequencies. Outstanding for <em>lasers, strobes,
                            or kick-drum synced dimmers</em>.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--accent);">Direct: Transients
                            (Flux):</strong> Reacts strictly to sharp changes in audio (snares, plucks, drops). Best for
                        <em>fast strobes, blinder blasts, or rapid resets</em>.
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--accent);">Cycle: Rhythm
                            (Beat/4th):</strong> Steps forward sequentially every beat or 4th beat. Use this for
                        <em>Gobo wheels, Color wheels, or step-based parameters</em> that should advance musically.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h4 style="color:var(--text); margin-top:20px; margin-bottom:10px;">Recommended Setups</h4>
                <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02); padding:10px; border-radius:6px; margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <ul style="padding-left:20px; margin:0;">
                        <li style="margin-bottom:6px;"><strong>Pan/Tilt:</strong> Map to <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">LFO</span> (Sine Wave) for smooth movement, or use <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">Beat</span> for stepped positions. Configure bounds to
                            prevent hitting walls.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom:6px;"><strong>Dimmer:</strong> Map to <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">Bass Energy</span> or use <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">Static Machine</span> to control via vibes.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom:6px;"><strong>Color Wheel:</strong> Map to <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">Cycle: Rhythm</span> for automatic stepping, or <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">LFO</span> (Sawtooth / Triangle) for sweeps.</li>
                        <li><strong>Strobe:</strong> Map a dedicated strobe channel to <span
                                style="color:var(--accent);">Transients (Flux)</span> so it only blasts on hard hits.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div style="margin-top:20px; text-align:center;">
